## 3. Test Questions to Verify All Edges

Copy and paste these prompts into the chatbot to test its various tools:

> [!TIP]
> **Web & Scraping Edge**
> - "Search the web for the latest news about OpenAI's new models released this week."
> - "Go to https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_Context_Protocol and summarize what it says."

> [!TIP]
> **Financial Edge**
> - "What is the current stock price of Microsoft (MSFT) and Nvidia (NVDA) right now?"
> - "Check Apple's stock price and tell me if it went up or down today."

> [!TIP]
> **GitHub Edge (Multi-tool test)**
> - "Give me a full analysis of the `facebook/react` repository. I want its stats, the latest 5 commits, and the top contributors."
> - "Search GitHub for repositories related to 'MCP server' written in Python."
> - "Tell me about the GitHub user profile for 'torvalds'."

> [!TIP]
> **Email Edge**
> - "Read my last 3 unseen emails."
> - "Draft an email to `example@gmail.com` with the subject 'Meeting Update' saying we need to reschedule for tomorrow."

> [!TIP]
> **Math & Logic Edge**
> - "Calculate `(12345 * 6789) / 42` exactly using your calculator tool."

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Complex Multi-Step Reasoning (The Ultimate Test)**
> - "First, check the live stock price of TSLA. Then, search the web to find out why TSLA's stock might be moving today. Finally, draft an email to `your-email@gmail.com` summarizing your findings."
